Message: Hi, I’m the NewsBreak Ad Assistant. How can I help?

Violation of Advertising Policy - The presentation of your website raises concerns regarding its credibility. We recommend improving the content and design of your landing page to create a more trustworthy and positive user experience.

It seems like your ad might have been flagged due to concerns about the credibility of your website's presentation. To address this, I recommend reviewing our Ad Policy and Guidelines to ensure your landing page aligns with our standards. You can find detailed information on our policies here: [Ad Policy](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25362604231053-Ad-Policy). If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
Under review. It usually takes 1-2 work days.

Yes, that's correct! The ad approval process typically takes between 1-2 business days. If your ad is still under review beyond this timeframe, it might be due to additional checks or requirements. If you have any concerns or need further assistance, feel free to let me know!

Violation of Advertising Policy - The presentation of your website raises concerns regarding its credibility. We recommend improving the content and design of your landing page to create a more trustworthy and positive user experience.

It looks like your ad was flagged due to concerns about the credibility of your website's presentation. To improve this, consider enhancing the content and design of your landing page to make it more trustworthy and user-friendly. For detailed guidelines on our advertising policies, please refer to our [Ad Policy](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25362604231053-Ad-Policy). If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
